## Test Writing Best Practices

### âœ… DO: Use ARIA-First Locators

```typescript
// âœ… Good: Stable, accessibility-friendly
await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' });
await page.getByLabel('Email Address');
await page.getByText('Welcome back!');
await page.getByTestId('checkout-button');

// âŒ Bad: Brittle, breaks on CSS changes
await page.locator('.btn-primary-large');
await page.locator('div > div > button:nth-child(3)');
```

### âœ… DO: Use Web-First Assertions (Auto-Retry)

```typescript
// âœ… Good: Waits up to 5s, retries automatically
await expect(page.getByText('Success')).toBeVisible();
await expect(page.getByRole('button')).toBeEnabled();

// âŒ Bad: No retry, fails immediately
expect(await page.getByText('Success').isVisible()).toBe(true);
```

### âœ… DO: Chain and Filter Locators

```typescript
// âœ… Good: Precise targeting within context
const product = page
  .getByRole('listitem')
  .filter({ hasText: 'Product 2' })
  .getByRole('button', { name: 'Add to cart' });

await product.click();
```

### âœ… DO: Use Fixtures for Shared Setup

```typescript
// tests/fixtures/auth.fixture.ts
import { test as base } from '@playwright/test';

export const test = base.extend({
  authenticatedPage: async ({ page }, use) => {
    // Reuse saved auth state
    await page.goto('/dashboard');
    await use(page);
  },
});
```

